## Context
Reviewer 1 additional question: the finance-development nexus (King & Levine
1993 → Aghion & Bolton → financial-deepening literature) is directly relevant to
why climate finance was framed as "mobilisation," "leverage," "crowding-in."

## Actions
1. Situate "blended finance" and "de-risking" vocabulary within this lineage in the crystallisation section.
2. Analyse the fact that climate finance developed as a largely self-contained accounting category, disconnected from these debates — make the disconnection itself an object of analysis.
3. Add refs (→ 0143).

## Exit criteria
- [ ] Blended-finance/de-risking vocabulary linked to the finance-development lineage
- [ ] The disconnection is analysed, not just noted
